dcterms:description: The dataset includes MRI scans of 783 infants, with structural, diffusion, and functional data acquired at the Evelina Newborn Imaging Centre. The imaging parameters include T2-weighted multi-slice fast spin-echo images and 3D MPRAGE scans, aimed at studying brain development and individual differences.

dcterms:description: This dataset provides a minimal processing pipeline for neonatal cortical surface reconstruction, facilitating the analysis of brain morphology and individual differences in infants.
